The Senior Prophet of Christ Mercyland Deliverance Ministry, Jeremiah Omoto Fufeyin, has charged Nigerians not to give up. He insisted that there is hope for the country despite prevailing challenges. The prophet, in a statement by his Publicity Secretary, Moses Akpovotiti, and his Media Aide, Engr. Tare Franklin, told Nigerians to remain hopeful in the face of the perilous times, adding God was set to transform the narrative the country. He entreated Nigerians to move closer to God ever. He also asked the country to focus on God’s promises and stay positive, amidst grueling realities, stressing no matter how hard things become: “they that wait on the Lord will have renewed strength; they will mount up with wings like eagles; they will run and not be weary; they will walk and not faint.” He also urged citizens to continue to pray for Nigeria, and to be pioneers of the change that we pray for, encouraging all to walk in love and unity with one another.